      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__v__demosaic_1gaec49738eff318af31f6412423d884cde" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void XVDemosaic_InterruptHandler</definition>
        <argsstring>(XV_demosaic *InstancePtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XVDemosaic_InterruptHandler</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_v__demosaic" kindref="compound">XV_demosaic</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Interrupt handler for the Demosaic IP core. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This handler clears pending interrupts and determines if the source is a frame done or frame ready signal. If the interrupt is valid, it calls the registered callback function for the corresponding event.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the Demosaic IP instance that just interrupted.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>None</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>The application is responsible for connecting this function to the interrupt system and providing callbacks using <ref refid="group__v__demosaic_1ga8adc7ef231a300187bbdb466e5d4a280" kindref="member">XVDemosaic_SetCallback()</ref> during initialization phase. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
